CHANGELOG — Do It List

Plain text. Append-only. Chronological (oldest first). Records scope, requirement, and doc-structure changes — not git commit history.

2026-05-05  M01-BaseApp scaffold landed; project pushed to https://github.com/n8bar/DoItList as a public MIT repo.
2026-05-05  Established doc hierarchy: ProductSpec.md as master spec, PLAN.md as master action list, CLAUDE.md as always-loaded primer above the spec/action split. Defined the "stay at your altitude" rule.
2026-05-06  Migrated milestone docs into docs/milestones/<milestone>/ subfolders. Codified the action-list hierarchy (Milestone -> Arc -> Worklist -> Item -> Subitem), dotted reference notation (m##.NN.NN.NN.NN), and branch naming (M##-<slug> + semantic prefixes).
2026-05-06  Added baseline ancillary docs: BACKLOG.md, FINDINGS.md, UX_GUARDRAILS.md, CHANGELOG.log. Added milestone-deadline convention (target dates required, approximate flags allowed).
2026-05-06  M02-UX-Overhaul scoped (target 2026-05-15). Two arcs: m02.01 UX guardrails audit & alignment; m02.02 design refinements (theme toggle, progress underbar, completion checkbox + cascade-confirm, collapsible children, inline description with em dash, project header bar, add-subtask signifier rework). Task `status` field removed from UI; schema column retained for possible later revival.
2026-05-06  Slimmed docs/PLAN.md by extracting Doc Roles and conventions (numbering, doc layout, specs vs. actions, deadlines) into new docs/README.md. Old PLAN §4 Branches and §5 Repo deleted as duplicates of CLAUDE.md. CLAUDE.md gained a pointer line directing agents to docs/README.md when adding docs or making structural decisions.
2026-05-07  Updated CLAUDE.md to current conventions: spec-first rule now points at docs/milestones/m##-<slug>/m##-<slug>.md (was docs/m##-*.md); branch naming switched from claude/<task> to M##-<slug> + semantic prefixes (fix/, chore/, docs/, spike/). Removed the "once the remote is set up" qualifier on the canonical-main rule since the remote is set up.
2026-05-07  Renamed Project to Orchard in ProductSpec.md vocabulary (cascades to Orchard member, "Multiple users may open the same Orchard"). Added Visual Metaphor section reserving tree/branch/leaf icons for Lists/parent-tasks/leaf-tasks and reserving Fruit/Crop names for a future goals concept. The code/schema rename to Orchard is a separate chore awaiting approval.
2026-05-07  Tightened docs/README.md numbering conventions: Arc headings use local number only (`### 1 — <name>`), and items must not prefix themselves with their own dotted reference. M02 doc reformatted to comply. Mirrored to core-doc-scaffold.
2026-05-07  Renamed Project to Orchard everywhere — DB (tables, columns, FK constraints, indexes, sequences via reversible rename migration), code (DoIt.Projects -> DoIt.Orchards module + schemas + function names + routes + PubSub topics), tests, M01 spec (retroactive), CLAUDE.md vocabulary, README.md. No data dropped. Three-commit chore branch: chore/orchard-rename.
2026-05-07  Tightened checkbox convention in docs/README.md: checkboxes mark actionable items only, never action-list titles or headings (Milestone, Arc, Worklist). Mirrored to core-doc-scaffold. Fixed misleading copy on the orchards index that implied 1:1 between Orchard and tree (now: Orchard holds multiple Lists; each List is a tree).
2026-05-07  Renamed Orchard to Initiative everywhere — second rename in two days, after deciding Orchard didn't communicate "purposeful work toward a goal". DB rename migration is reversible; no data dropped. Code, schemas, routes, tests, M01 spec (retroactive), M02 spec (Initiative-level progress underbar, item 9 grove-icon addition), ProductSpec metaphor section, CLAUDE.md vocabulary, README.md, PLAN.md M01+M02 rows. Three-commit chore branch: chore/initiative-rename. Botanical icon metaphor preserved at the visual layer (Lucide trees/tree/branch/leaf for Initiative/List/parent-task/leaf-task).
2026-05-08  Tightened FINDINGS.md conventions. Rule 2 status definitions now point at rule 6 for promotion's precise meaning. Rule 6 sharpens promoted as "an unchecked action item owns the fix at the moment of status change". New rule 7: pre-scoped refinements already covered by an upcoming milestone/arc are not findings. New rule 8: two paths to a fix — promote (action list owns the fix) or fix inline (the finding owns the fix via `**[ ] fix:**` ↔ `**[x] fix:**` checkbox); inline can escalate to promotion if scope grows. Mirrored to core-doc-scaffold.
